results.name: Number of primes in the interval [9n, 10n].
link: FUNG Cheok Yin, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(n) = n/log(n) + (1 + log(3^18/10^10))*n/log(n)^2 + O(n/log(n)^3) as n -> infinity. - _Robert Israel_, Jul 12 2017
mathematica: Join[{0}, Table[PrimePi[10 n] - PrimePi[9 n], {n, 2, 100}]] (* _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jul 13 2017 *)
